properties.campaignPrologue: "You fell asleep for a while rocked by the sea. Then, a gentle hit awakens you: the ship hits the dock of a castle harbor."

properties.onTalk: "Oh. Someone came to save us! Please forgive my selfishness. I'm Paulitico, this castle humble librarian. We don't have much time... can you follow me to central square on the west, please?"
"Our King gifted its best politician with the Guardian Stone, in order to wisely rule our lands. But, well... Something went wrong..."
"After inviting the leaders of all the guilds, he trapped us all inside the castle and skeletons started appearing, killing many of us. We have to escape and I've a plan."
"First we've to open the west wing of the castle. There should be a switch on the western dock on south. I'm not a fighter... can you go there for me?"
properties.onTalked: "The dock is on south west. Good luck, traveller!"

properties.onTalk: "You did it! Your heart is as strong as your heart, traveller. Now you've to find the western library. There is a book lying on the ground: that's a magic switch! Just read the first page and come back here."
properties.onTalked: "Find the book lying on the ground and read it!"

properties.onTalk: "Humans used to live isolated but, due to the lack of a particular skill or resource, they started fighting each other. After years of blood, they organized themselves in small groups..."

"I've read that book thousands of times. Being selfish drives only toward destruction, isn't it? Let's move on. There is another library and book on the east wing. Do the same thing you did before, please."
properties.onTalked: "Find the book lying on the ground and read it!"

properties.onTalk: "Humans used to live in small villages but, due to their thirst for richness, they started fighting each other. After years of blood, they organized themselves in larger villages..."
"Why this door is still closed? Looks like that the magic lock isn't working properly here. Are we destined to die here...?"
"The doors of the northen gates has been swapped as requested. Nobody noticed us. Our experiment is precious, we won't commit the same error again."

properties.onDefeated: "Aaaghh! I just wanted food! Food! Food! Gime me food! I'm dying! Aaaarghh!"

properties.onTalk: "Ugh... Food? You brought me food? Are you food? Food? Food? Foood?"
"This... This door needs the third book. You... you can find it into a jail on the west side. But... Why there are all these trees sorrounding the door? What... Why?"
"Humans used to live in cities but, due to their thirst for power, they started fighting each other. After years of blood, they organized themselves in nations..."

"Traveller! The door is still stuck... I truly don't know what's happening here. Anyway I've heard a loud crash coming from the south east of the castle... and... well... a terribly scary roar. What... what was that?"
"Are you going to free meee? Thaaank yoou... Please, come nearbye... Breeeak my chaiins..."

properties.onDefeated: "You... you die... like me die... I'm experiment... Failed experiment... but... But you good experiment? Arggh..."

properties.onTalk: "Here. There is... our politician. We've to... persuade him to open the castle gates. The door switch is stuck... Can you have a look over there?"

properties.onSwitchPressed: "Paulitico: Sage! We are going to give a new form to the whole world... destroy every form of society and replace with our... Sage?! No, Sage, No! Aaaagh! *crackle*"

properties.onTalk: "Trees... and destruction... interesting reaction, indeed. Follow me, the last door is over there."
"I am the guardian golem, the defender of the humans, the eraser of every mistake they made. Why? Why you want to fight justice?"

properties.onDefeated: "Humanity... is so violent... We guardians... have to keep them from killing eachother... To kill violence. But my time is up... now... It's your turn."

properties.onTalk: "Thanks to the Gods! We've seen your little ship docked and came here. We gladly found again Brother Salivello... And I think we've to thank you again. You are our savior, traveller."
"I was on my ship with the monk here... we were looking for our missing leaders and, luckly, we've found them thanks to you. Your ship is ready to leave. Where are you going to go this time?"

properties.campaignEpilogue: "Golems. And more golems. The smell of their blood is becoming awkwardly familiar and pleasant to you. With the grateful voices of your friends echoing in the ears, you leave once more. Waiting for the next adventure..."

properties.onTalk: "Studies so far proven that people entrusted with the Guardian Stones gains unlimited power. Despite that, they are still mortal. It's an interesting contraddiction we can use as advantage."

"The Guardian Stone reacts with the dead owner body, turning him into a giant golem. He loses his memories but his previous sense of justice remains intact. Is this a viable way of manipulating them?"
"Guardian Stones are hard to replicate but every time a golem is spawned, another Guardian Stone appears nearby. Our pact with travellers played a key role on retrieving them."

"We don't know from where the Guardian Stone came from. The depictions of them we've found in this ancient sanctuary suggests that these stones were used by Gods for controlling the will of leaders, guardians and heroes."
"His body is cold and lifeless."

properties.campaignPrologue: "After few days of sailing, you catch sight of a greenish island at the horizon. Food and water are running out, so you decide to stop and resupply."

properties.onTalk: "East: Old town - North: Royal castle - West: Meadow"
"A human woman came here not long ago. She says that she's the Traveller Guild chief. Honestly, I don't care - unless she pay me for guarding her shop."
"Welcome traveller. The Elven Lands became very dangerous so be careful."

"You must be the human that saved the dwaves from skeletons. Your reputation precedes you. I need your help. My daughter Castilla went on the north two days ago and isn't back. Bring her to me, please!"
"The skeleton invaded our lands... Have we angered the Gods?"
"North: Castle woods"
"Fantastic. My father sent someone to rescue me. Why he doesn't mind his own business? So who will climb the castle walls? Very well. I'll go back to the goddamn town."

"Castilla, you've finally made your mind and came back to me. I... I was so worried. Please, don't try to get into the castle anymore, It's too dangerous... Don't do anything reckless and let me handle the question."
"My high sovereign... Your castle has been occupied by a stupid leafy golem and you're doing nothing but waiting in the old town? Why? Why we can't go back home? Answer me! Don't leave!"

properties.onTalked: "You've to excuse me. I need some time."

properties.onTalk: "Reelfo said that I've to stay put... but there might be something I can do! Sorry, traveller. I have an errand to run. Farewell."

"That... that elven girl was in such a hurry... Brother Salivello is gone missing again. He went to the west side of the castle but isn't back. After I've explained that to her, she ran away all of the sudden..."
properties.onTalked: "Oh, my. What... What can I do now?"

properties.onTalk: "Welcome traveller. Our sovereign was waiting for you. Please, come in."
properties.onTalked: "I'm honored to serve our sovereign... but I wonder why we're not trying to get back the castle..."

properties.onTalk: "Ah! Ah! You are way too slow, traveller. You have to do better than this if you want to stop me again!"

"I... I was looking for Brother Salivello but, after running from skeletons, I fell exhausted here. I waited for help but a young elven came and just ran away saying anything. Anyway, thank you. I'll cast a Blessed Circle for you."
"Hey! I just don't care about that suicidal monk. I just want to climb the castle walls... and if you don't stop following me I swear that I'll put an arrow through your head!"
"Ow. Hello again, adventurer. I've... just found this switch that opens the castle gates in order to take the precious... freedom, yes. Well. I'm going back to the town. Thank you!"

properties.onSwitchLocked: "What Brother Salivello is doing here? I've to ask him."
properties.onSwitchPressed: "Something is rumbling in front of the castle..."

properties.onTalk: "That monk was helpful after all... I wonder why my father forgot to mention anything about this button... Now I've to sneak into the castle before he know it!"
"Thank you for saving Brother Salivello again. He loves bringing the faith in the Gods to the people, so he often put himself in danger."
"Castilla! Castilla! Don't... don't go there! You... Don't do that! Oh, Gods... Please, traveller! Bring her out of the castle! I'm begging you!"
"Another door? Ack. There should be a switch on the Eastern Tower..."

"So, traveller. Do you have decided to help me? Are you looking for the castle treasures? Or are you just curious about the castle golem? Anyway, we need to trigger the Western Tower switch in order to open this door... Please, help me."

"The treasure is over there, traveller. You deserve it. I hear more monsters behind this door but I can defeat them by myself: I've to conquer the throne room alone and show my father that I'm not worthless. Thank you for your help."
"I am the guardian golem, the defender of the nature, the true meaning of life on this earth. Why? Why you want to fight justice?"
"Th... That... golem... She... She looks like... Mom... What... What is happening? Why that golem has my mother face? Why dad? WHY?"

properties.onDefeated: "I was... defending the life... and I've just found my death. I hope that someone will take my place, one day. But... That eyes. The eyes of that elven girl... I've seen them... The Guardian Stone... My beloved husband..."

properties.onTalk: "I can't understand... why that golem had my mother face? Father said she should be in a safe place far away... he lied to me? I can't find him anywhere... Anyway, your quest is over, traveller. Thank you."
properties.onTalked: "Have a nice trip, traveller. And thank you."

properties.campaignEpilogue: "Another golem died by the blade of your sword. Is this ship going to bring you to them in order to slay em all? With this doubt in mind, you step into your ship and set sail."

properties.onTalk: "Castilla... ugh... forgive... me..."
"I... I don't have any more reason for living... Please, let me die in this sweet and deadly meadow alone."

properties.campaignPrologue: "You regain consciousness on a strangely familiar small lifeboat docked on the seaside. After contemplating the sky, you decide to stand up and exploring a bit."

properties.onTalk: "Dwarf village."
"Ugh. The dwarf village has been attacked by skeletons. I... I managed to escape and isolate the city using my Guards Seal... Take it. I don't... need... it anymore."

properties.onClosed: "Looks like some kind of key is needed."
"Looks like some kind of key is needed."

properties.onTalk: "You! Are you coming from the outside? So that damn door has been opened! That gutless guard closed us into this cave with the monsters. Now we've to found the others!"
"Please, wayfarer. You have to save Brother Salivello... he is exploring the west side of the caves looking for an exit. All I can offer you is this Belssed Circle for your rest."
"Guards my ass. They trapped us here!"
"Ow. Hello, adventurer. I'm Brother Salivello and I was... I was looking for an exit, yes. I've finally found this chest... for you. Take it as your reward. I'm going back to the village. Thanks..."
"Brother Salivello is back to the church safe and sound. Thank you wayfarer! Now I hope that the Travellers Guild chief is safe too..."
"The guards ran away..."
"I've searched the Traveller Guild chief on the south-east of the caves but I failed. All I've found is this key - take it! Please, help me!"
"Oh, GREAT! Damn. Someone sent you to bring me back? Okay, I'm going back. But I'll kill that damn dwarf one day!"
"Wendy is so furious... the dwarf village governor stolen some weapons from her goods and ran into the cave. He must hiding somewhere."
"I hope Wernogow is alive. I've stocked some food in our hidden shelters... but I hope he won't need them."
"You came for me, yes? I was looking for a way out for my people but skeletons attacked me. You look strong - We've to talk. Let's meet at our village."

"We gave the dwarf Guardian Stone to our strongest warrior... but he turned into a rock golem and started attacking. Then the golem went to the North East Maze. I've opened the door for you. Have a look there. Good luck!"
"Ugh... I just... managed to close the west side of the caves... Please... keep that area sealed. Don't give my Guards Seal to anyone..."
"I am the guardian golem, the defender of the skeletons, the people that lived these lands way before the living. Why? Why you want to fight justice?"

properties.onDefeated: "Why... Why I've been entrusted with the Guardian Stone and then betrayed like this? But my people will live on... and take back what was theirs."

properties.onTalk: "You saved our village and my people! Do you want to be our new guardian? Ah! Ah! Ah! I shouldn't ask travellers to stay. Here. This is a little reward for your mission. Good luck on your journey!"
"Are you going to leave with your boat? I'll leave the dwarf village soon too. Thank you for saving our boss!"
"We've prepared your boat on the south beach. Thank you for helping these people... and for saving our Brother Salivello."

properties.campaignEpilogue: "This adventure made you stronger and valorous. Is this the beginning of a new life? With this ambitius thought in mind, you retract the moorings and leave."

properties.onTalk: "Rierogher stolen our Guardian Stone, saying that, as the strongest dwarf warrior, he deserved it. I had to stop him at any cost: now his body lies buried in these caves."
"Wernogow usually takes note of everything important on his journal. I wonder why he isn't doing that right now."
